# Forms Rules

## React Hook Form
- Use React Hook Form for all forms
- Use Zod schemas for validation via `@hookform/resolvers/zod`
- Extract form logic into custom hooks when complex
- Use `Form` component from `@shared/ui/form` (shadcn wrapper)

## Form Structure
- Define Zod schema for form validation
- Use `zodResolver` from `@hookform/resolvers/zod`
- Use `useForm` hook with proper typing
- Connect form fields using `register` or `Controller` component

## Validation
- Always validate on both client and server side
- Use Zod schemas for type-safe validation
- Provide clear, user-friendly error messages
- Show validation errors inline near form fields

## Form Components
- Use shadcn form components from `@shared/ui/`
- Use `FormField`, `FormItem`, `FormLabel`, `FormControl`, `FormDescription`, `FormMessage` components
- Wrap inputs with proper form components for error handling

## Best Practices
- Use `Controller` for complex inputs (date pickers, rich text editors)
- Use `register` for simple inputs
- Handle form submission with `handleSubmit`
- Show loading state during submission
- Reset form after successful submission
- Handle errors from API responses

## Example Pattern
```typescript
const formSchema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email(),
  password: z.string().min(8),
});

const form = useForm<z.infer<typeof formSchema>>({
  resolver: zodResolver(formSchema),
});

const onSubmit = async (values: z.infer<typeof formSchema>) => {
  // Handle submission
};
```
